    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your<strong> chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes </strong>(skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges, leaving the skins on (this helps them cook quicker!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potato</strong>,<strong> red onion wedges</strong> and <strong>cherry tomatoes </strong>to a baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Add your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 25-30 min or until the vegetables are soft and the potatoes are crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>caprese bake</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate your cheddar cheese</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the chicken with your <strong>traditional Italian pesto</strong> and <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 18-20 min or until the cheese is golden and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy pesto chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables are done, carefully cut off the root, then remove and discard the skins of your red onion</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pesto-chicken-with-caprese-bake/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>pesto chicken</strong> with the <strong>caprese bake</strong> to the side</p><p>Pour over any <strong>remaining chicken juices</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
